"{\"uid\": \"cyclingnews.com-races-olympic-games-2024-track-cycling-men-s-team-sprint-preview\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"  Teams compete for gold on August 6  When you purchase through links on our site, we may earn an affiliate commission.Here's how it works.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 139, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The latest race content, interviews, features, reviews and expert buying guides, direct to your inbox!\", \"from\": 141, \"to\": 243, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You are now subscribed  Your newsletter sign-up was successful  The second medal event in track cycling at the Paris Olympics, the men's team sprint pits teams of three powerful riders against each other in a test of who can compete three laps (750 metres) the quickest.\", \"from\": 245, \"to\": 515, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Dutch team have been the dominant squad in team sprinting since 2018 when they claimed their first world title, and with the powerhouse Harrie Lavreysen in their midst, the trio have won five of the past six Worlds.\", \"from\": 517, \"to\": 736, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 521, \"end\": 526, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"score\": 0.9999040208405623, \"rank\": 7.16820398377487e-05, \"text\": \"Dutch\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\"}, {\"begin\": 657, \"end\": 673, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harrie_Lavreysen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Harrie Lavreysen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harrie_Lavreysen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harrie_Lavreysen\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lavreysen, Roy van den Berg and Matthijs B\\u00fcchli set theOlympic Record(41.369 seconds) en route to claiming gold in Tokyo, and hold the World Record (41.225 seconds) set in 2020.\", \"from\": 738, \"to\": 915, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 749, \"end\": 765, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roy_van_den_Berg\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Roy van den Berg\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roy_van_den_Berg\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roy_van_den_Berg\"}, {\"begin\": 749, \"end\": 765, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roy_van_den_Berg\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Roy van den Berg\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roy_van_den_Berg\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Roy_van_den_Berg\"}, {\"begin\": 770, \"end\": 778, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matthijs_Maris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999922693, \"rank\": 7.86708636381761e-12, \"text\": \"Matthijs\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matthijs_Maris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matthijs_Maris\"}, {\"begin\": 853, \"end\": 858, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.8516605542547449, \"rank\": 0.17357379474212292, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The men's team sprint qualifying begins on August 5 at 13:09 local time at the Saint-Quentin-en-Yvelines velodrome.\", \"from\": 917, \"to\": 1032, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"After being seeded in qualifying, the eight teams will face off 1st vs 8th, 2nd vs 7th, 3rd vs 6th and 4th vs 5th fastest in the first round of racing on August 6 at 12:59 CET.\", \"from\": 1034, \"to\": 1210, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The top four will move onto the finals on August 6 at 13:55 with the top two racing for gold and silver and third and fourth competing for the bronze medal.\", \"from\": 1212, \"to\": 1368, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"While the Dutch have been so dominant for years, they are not unbeatable.\", \"from\": 1370, \"to\": 1443, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1380, \"end\": 1385, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"score\": 0.9999040208405623, \"rank\": 7.16820398377487e-05, \"text\": \"Dutch\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Australians managed to get the better of them at Worlds in 2022 but the two team's have not been head-to-head since Australia fell short in the Glasgow Worlds last August.\", \"from\": 1444, \"to\": 1619, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1564, \"end\": 1573, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_cricket_team\", \"score\": 0.4393881371755121, \"rank\": 0.6641981863404536, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_cricket_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_cricket_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They were just 0.045 seconds apart in the finals.\", \"from\": 1620, \"to\": 1669, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The latest race content, interviews, features, reviews and expert buying guides, direct to your inbox!\", \"from\": 1671, \"to\": 1773, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Leigh Hoffman, Matthew Glaetzer and Matthew Richardson will be out for revenge in Paris, and it's hard to imagine any other team getting close.\", \"from\": 1775, \"to\": 1918, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1775, \"end\": 1780, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leigh_Centurions\", \"score\": 0.9999831545105792, \"rank\": 1.6841444255755993e-05, \"text\": \"Leigh\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leigh_Centurions\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leigh_Centurions\"}, {\"begin\": 1781, \"end\": 1788, \"title\": \"http:/